<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="activity-n">activity <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /æk'tɪvəti/    美 /ækˈtɪvəti/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c">1.★ <strong>[C] [常用复数] (出于爱好的) 活动</strong></h4>
<p>a thing that you do for interest or pleasure：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>outdoor activities</strong>
户外活动</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Sailing is an activity I much enjoy. 
帆船运动是我非常喜爱的活动。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>After-class activities are treated as an essential part of school life. 
课外活动被视为学校生活不可或缺的一部分。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c-u">2.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] (有组织的，有目的的) 活动</strong></h4>
<p>a thing that you do in order to achieve a particular aim：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>fund-raising activities
筹款活动</p></div>

<h4 id="3-u">3.★ <strong>[U] (正在进行的或正在做的) 活动</strong></h4>
<p>a situation in which sth is happening or a lot of things are happening or being done：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The streets were noisy and full of activity. 
街道上一片喧嚣与忙碌。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Regular physical activity helps to control your weight.
经常活动身体有助于控制体重。</p></div></div>